<head>FLAY</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>WHIP</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">鞭打 </item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>STRIKE USING a WHIP.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Cè 策 refers to flaying an animal or a person with a bamboo whip, typically to urge the creature flayed on.</p>
<p>2. Biān 鞭 refers to flaying someone with a leather strap whip.</p>
<p>3. Pū 扑 "beat" is sometimes said to involve the whip, but I have not seen any clear evidence for this.</p>
<p>NB: For chī 笞 "strike with a bamboo cane or stick" and the like see STRIKE.</p>
        </div>
